"35:1:3" : {s: 35, a: 1, w: 3, r: "فطر", t: "فَاطِرِ", l: "فَاطِر", lc: 6, tl: "fāṭiri", lb: "সৃষ্টিকর্তা",e: "Originator", b: "(যিনি) স্রষ্টা", i: "malaikat", f: 3, rm: "to create out of nothing, cleave/split/crack/break, be broken into pieces, cleave asunder, begin to create. fitrat - natural disposition or constitution with which a child is created. The faculty of knowing God and capability of accepting the religion of truth, religion. fatir  -creator, one of the names of Allah. futur - crack/flaw. munfatirun - split one, cloven one, one rent asunder.", ag: "أسم فاعل", eg: "Noun Active participle", tag: "N", pos: "N", att: "ACT_PCPL", qual: "GEN", deg: "", gen: "M", num: "", mood: "", lu: "فَطَرَ،فَاطِرُ،مُنفَطِرٌۢ"},
